-- Ex-Goldman trader Pierre-Henri Flamand joins Man Group
-- 
-- Wed May 07, 2014 03:52AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 7 (Reuters) - Former head of proprietary trading at Goldman Sachs Pierre-Henri Flamand has joined listed UK hedge fund Man Group <EMG.L> as a senior portfolio manager, the company said on Wednesday.

Flamand will join the company in its GLG unit during 2014 and focus on a "global catalyst-driven strategy across the capital structure", Man said in a statement.